Seeks relative to the current position.

This is equivalent to `self.seek(SeekFrom::Current(offset))` but doesnâ€™t return the new position which can allow some implementations such as [`BufReader`](struct.BufReader.html "struct std::io::BufReader") to perform more efficient seeks.

##### [Â§](#example-3)Example

```
use std::{
    io::{self, Seek},
    fs::File,
};

fn main() -> io::Result<()> {
    let mut f = File::open("foo.txt")?;
    f.seek_relative(10)?;
    assert_eq!(f.stream_position()?, 10);
    Ok(())
}
```

